24 SECTION 15. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
25 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
26 REIMBURSEMENT AND REFUND TO EXPENDITURE. Funds allocated and expended by any
27 Agency, Authority, Board, Commission, Council, Department, Division, Office,
28 or Subdivision of any state agency for the payment of approved claims
29 adjudicated through the State Claims Commission and approved by the Arkansas
30 Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee when the General Assembly is in
31 session, shall be reimbursed from the funds from which the Agency, Authority,
32 Board, Commission, Council, Department, Division, Office, or Subdivision
33 draws its support.
34 The monies shall be deposited no later than June 30 of the following
35 fiscal year from which the original payment of claim expense was incurred by
36 the state agency, as a refund to expenditure, to the credit of the fund from
5 04-01-2025 16:24:45 MAH020

As Engrossed: S3/3/25 H4/1/25 SB132
1 which the original expenditure was made.
2
3 SECTION 16. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
4 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. CARRYOVER
5 OF CLAIMS. Any state agency which is affected by the allowed claim(s)
6 provided for in this Act, and whose fund for the 2023-2024 2024-2025 fiscal
7 year are insufficient to allow for the payment of said claim(s) before June
8 30, 2024 2025, is hereby authorized, upon certification by the Chief Fiscal
9 Officer of the State, to make payment of said claim(s) after July 1, 2024
10 2025, from funds appropriated for the 2024-2025 2025-2026 fiscal year.
11
12 SECTION 17. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
13 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
14 DISBURSING OFFICER. The Clerk of the State Claims Commission is hereby made
15 the disbursing officer for the purpose of paying the claims appropriated by
16 this Act. The Clerk of the State Claims Commission is hereby authorized to
17 receive all warrants prepared under the provisions of this Act from the
18 Auditor of State and to distribute same to the claimants.
19
20 SECTION 18. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
21 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. ARKANSAS
22 DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN SERVICES CLAIMS. For any claims in this Act appropriated
23 to the Department of Human Services, the Clerk of the State Claims Commission
24 shall consult with the Department of Human Services and the Chief Fiscal
25 Officer of the State to determine the division and funds to which liability
26 should be assigned and from which the warrants shall be drawn. The Clerk of
27 the State Claims Commission shall initiate the appropriate transfers as may
28 be required and as approved by the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State.
29
30 SECTION 19. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
31 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. ARKANSAS
32 DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH CLAIMS. For any claims in this Act appropriated to the
33 Department of Health, the Clerk of the State Claims Commission shall consult
34 with the Department of Health and the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State to
35 determine the division and funds to which liability should be assigned and
36 from which the warrants shall be drawn. The Clerk of the State Claims
