4 SECTION 20. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
5 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. CLAIMS
6 FROM CASH FUNDS. In the event that any claim authorized herein is determined
7 to be a valid claim against the State and the claim is to be paid from funds
8 not in the State Treasury, the Clerk of the State Claims Commission shall
9 notify the agency against which the claim is to be charged of the amount of
10 such claims. Upon receipt of such notification, the state agency shall
11 forth-with deliver a check to the Clerk of the State Claims Commission who
12 shall deposit the same as a nonrevenue receipt into the Miscellaneous
13 Revolving Fund from which he shall disburse the amount of the claim to the
14 claimant.
15
16 SECTION 21. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
17 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
18 EMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION CLAIMS. The Clerk of the State Claims Commission
19 shall not distribute any warrants prepared under the provisions of this Act
20 for awards made by the Arkansas State Claims Commission for employment
21 compensation claims. Upon the award by the State Claims Commission of an
22 employment compensation claim, the Clerk of the State Claims Commission shall
23 notify the affected state agency and the Department of Finance and
24 Administration - Office of Personnel Management of such amounts that are due
25 and payable. The affected state agency shall then process the award through
26 the State Mechanized Payroll System.
27
28 SECTION 22. COMPLIANCE WITH OTHER LAWS. Disbursement of funds
29 authorized by this act shall be limited to the appropriation for such agency
30 and funds made available by law for the support of such appropriations; and
31 the restrictions of the State Procurement Law, the General Accounting and
32 Budgetary Procedures Law, the Revenue Stabilization Law, the Regular Salary
33 Procedures and Restrictions Act, or their successors, and other fiscal
34 control laws of this State, where applicable, and regulations promulgated by
35 the Department of Finance and Administration, as authorized by law, shall be
36 strictly complied with in disbursement of said funds.
7 04-01-2025 16:24:45 MAH020

As Engrossed: S3/3/25 H4/1/25 SB132
1
2 SECTION 23. LEGISLATIVE INTENT. It is the intent of the General
3 Assembly that any funds disbursed under the authority of the appropriations
4 contained in this act shall be in compliance with the stated reasons for
5 which this act was adopted, as evidenced by the Agency Requests, Executive
6 Recommendations and Legislative Recommendations contained in the budget
7 manuals prepared by the Department of Finance and Administration, letters, or
8 summarized oral testimony in the official minutes of the Arkansas Legislative
9 Council or Joint Budget Committee which relate to its passage and adoption.
10
11 SECTION 24. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
12 General Assembly, that payees listed in this Act may be entitled to the sums
13 appropriated and transferred to herein, and that they have been deprived of
14 the use of these funds for a long period of time, and that further delay in
15 paying these just debts of the state would do harm to the reputation of the
16 State of Arkansas. Therefore, an emergency is hereby declared to exist and
17 this Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public peace,
18 health and safety shall be in full force and effect from and after the date
19 of its passage and approval.
20 If the bill is neither approved nor vetoed by the Governor, it shall become
21 effective on the expiration of the period of time during which the Governor
22 may veto the bill. If the bill is vetoed by the Governor and the veto is
23 overridden, it shall become effective on the date the last house overrides
24 the veto.
